# SAPCyTI — Agent Rules

You are working on SAPCyTI, a system for postgraduate administration at UAM Iztapalapa.

## Architecture

- Modular monolith, hexagonal architecture (ports & adapters), DDD
- Backend: Java 21, Spring Boot 3.x, PostgreSQL 16, Flyway, MapStruct
- Frontend: Angular, TypeScript strict, separate repo (sapcyti-spa)
- Multi-tenant via `X-Graduate-Id` header

## Backend conventions

- Base package: `mx.uam.sapcyti`
- Modules: `configuration`, `identity`, `academic`, `offering`, `enrollment`
- Layers per module: `domain/{model,port/in,port/out,service}`, `application/service`, `infrastructure/{adapter/in,adapter/out,mapper,acl,security}`
- Domain model uses JPA annotations directly — NO separate Entity classes
- MapStruct for DTO↔Domain only (compile-time)
- DTOs: `{Name}Request`, `{Name}Response` in `adapter/in/dto/`
- Ports: `{Name}RepositoryPort` (out), `{Name}InputPort` (in)
- Migrations: `V{N}__{description}.sql`
- Logging: SLF4J only, NO `System.out.println`
- Cross-module: ID references only, via output ports

## Frontend conventions

- Shell + Core + Shared + Feature modules (lazy-loaded)
- i18n: `@ngx-translate`, keys in `assets/i18n/{lang}.json`
- Tailwind CSS, PrimeNG, CSS puro (sin preprocesadores), responsive-first

## DevOps

- GitFlow, Conventional Commits
- CI: lint → build → test → security → coverage (≥80%)
- Docker multi-stage, env vars only

## SDD workflow

- Every task requires an approved spec (🔵) before coding
- Specs live in `sdd/specs/iteration-{N}/`
- PR message format: `feat({module}): SPEC-{NNN} {description}`

## What to load per task type

| Task | Load | Do NOT load |
|------|------|-------------|
| Implement spec | Only `sdd/specs/.../SPEC-XXX.md` | Architecture.md full, sdd/theory, all HUs |
| Write spec | phase task + `design/Architecture-INDEX.md` section + HU + `technologies/{area}.md` + `sdd/domain/` BC artifacts + SPEC-TEMPLATE | Full Architecture.md, unrelated specs |
| Review code | Spec + `technologies/testing.md` | Architecture.md full |
| ADD / architecture | `design/ArchitecturalDrivers.md`, `IterationPlan.md`, Architecture sections | Individual specs |

See [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) for full protocol.

## What to load (legacy short form)

- **Implementing a spec:** Read ONLY the spec file. It is self-contained.
- **Writing a spec:** Use `design/Architecture-INDEX.md` to pick sections, then read those sections of `design/Architecture.md` + HU + `technologies/{area}.md` + `sdd/domain/`
- **Reviewing code:** Read the spec + `technologies/testing.md`

## Do NOT

- Import across bounded contexts — use output ports
- Add framework imports to domain layer beyond `jakarta.persistence.*`
- Hardcode strings in Angular — use i18n keys
- Use `@SpringBootTest` for unit tests
- Create files outside the scope defined in the spec
